definition: a type of standing harp, smaller than konghou 箜篌, with 5-25 strings

sentences.english: Moses therefore took the money of them that were above, and whom they had redeemed from the Levites.
sentences.chinese: 梅瑟就为那超过肋未人数而应赎回的人，征收了赎金。

sentences.english: And thou shalt set upon the table loaves of proposition in my sight always.
sentences.chinese: 在桌上于上主前摆上供饼，如上主吩咐梅瑟的。

sentences.english: After the blood of the guilty was shed, the Lord said to Moses and to Eleazar the son of Aaron, the priest.
sentences.chinese: 上主对梅瑟和大司祭亚郎的儿子厄肋阿匝尔说。

sentences.english: The Lord spoke to Moses, saying.
Originally God spoke these words through Moses to Israel in the desert.
sentences.chinese: 这话原是天主透过梅瑟向在旷野中的以民说的。

sentences.english: Q2: Approximately how many years were there between Abraham and Moses?
sentences.chinese: 亚巴郎和梅瑟大约相隔多久？

sentences.english: And the Lord spoke to Moses in the desert of Sinai, saying.
sentences.chinese: 上主在西乃旷野训示梅瑟说。

sentences.english: And Aaron and his sons did all things which the Lord spoke by the hand of Moses.
sentences.chinese: 凡上主藉梅瑟所吩咐的事，亚郎和他的儿子都做了。

sentences.english: And all the multitude of the children of Israel going out from the presence of Moses.
sentences.chinese: 于是以色列子民全会众离开梅瑟而去。

sentences.english: Moses hid his face: for he durst not look at God.
sentences.chinese: 梅瑟因为怕看见天主，就把脸遮起来。

sentences.english: Moses had given the tribe of Reuben a part of the land according to their clans.
sentences.chinese: 梅瑟给勒乌本支派，按照他们的家族，分了一份产业。

sentences.english: Whom Moses and Aaron took with all the multitude of the common people.
sentences.chinese: 梅瑟和亚郎就带着这些提名派定的人。

sentences.english: And the Lord said to Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 上主在埃及国训示梅瑟和亚郎说。

sentences.english: Moses therefore wrote the canticle and taught it to the children of Israel.
sentences.chinese: 梅瑟遂在那一天写下了这篇诗歌，教给了以色列子民。

sentences.english: And Moses gave a possession to the children of Ruben according to their kindreds.
sentences.chinese: 梅瑟给勒乌本支派，按照他们的家族，分了一份产业。

sentences.english: Moses numbered them as the Lord had commanded.
sentences.chinese: 于是梅瑟就照上主吩咐的命令，统计了他们。

definition: Abraham (name)/Abraham, father of Judaism and Islam in the Bible and Quran/same as Ibrahim 易卜拉辛
Jehovah (biblical name for God, Hebrew: YHWH)/compare Yahweh 雅威[Ya3 wei1] and God 上帝[Shang4 di4]
Gideon (name, from Judges 6:11-ffoll.)/also written 吉迪恩
